00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:08.000
In one of the more shocking civil rights incidents of the year,

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:13.000
Georgia State Representative Park Cannon was arrested last Thursday

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:18.000
for knocking on a door to the governor's office in the state capital,

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:23.000
as he signed into law of bill restricting voting access.

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:27.000
Cannon was charged with two felonies,

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.000
obstructing law enforcement officers,

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:34.000
and disrupting a general assembly session.

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:39.000
The arrest was witnessed by a fellow state representative, Eric Atomas.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:47.000
But you're going to tell me that you arrested a city who stayed represented for nothing.

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:51.000
She didn't do anything but not for the governor's door.

00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:58.000
I'm tired, I'm so dead, I'm so tired, protected, served, all.

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:04.000
Representative Cannon was released Thursday night to a cheering crowd of supporters.

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:10.000
We've had with Park! We've had with Park! We've had with Park! We've had with Makatteri!

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:22.000
And that crowd was Cannon's pastor,那個 Senator Rafael Warnock,

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:29.000
who called the days' events a desperate attempt to squeeze the people out of their own democracy,

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:31.000
democracy in quote.

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:36.000
We're grateful for those who are here in support of Representative Cannon.

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:39.000
She is an outstanding public servant.

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:40.000
We're praying for her.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:43.000
We're praying for her family.

00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:47.000
But we are praying also for Georgia.

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:52.000
And for the soul of our democracy, we are witnessing right now a kind of wrestling in

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:55.000
the soul of Georgia.

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:58.000
Will we go forward or will we go backwards?

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:06.000
We will not allow a few politicians in their craving lust for power to take us back.

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:13.000
The democracy doesn't belong to the politicians it belongs to the people.

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:18.000
In a midnight tweet, Cannon wrote, I've been released from jail.

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:23.000
I am not the first Georgian to be arrested for fighting voter suppression.

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:29.000
I'd love to say I'm the last, but we know that isn't true.

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:35.000
Condemnation of the arrest and of Georgia's new election law was widespread coming even

00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:37.000
from the White House.

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:41.000
This is press secretary, Jen Saki.

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:48.000
I think anyone who saw that video would have been deeply concerned by the actions that

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:54.000
were taken by law enforcement to arrest her when she simply by the video that was provided

00:04:54.000 --> 00:05:00.000
seemed to be knocking on the door to see if she could watch a bill being signed into

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:01.000
law.

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:08.000
The largest concern here, obviously beyond her being treated in the manner she was, which

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:13.000
is of course of great concern, is the law that was put into place.

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:20.000
Cannon's attorney, Gerald Griggs, told CNN on Friday that Cannon is shaken but resolved

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:26.000
to fight for justice and fight for the voices of the people she represents.

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:29.000
Park Cannon has served in the State House for years.

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:35.000
She's always been an advocate for the disenfranchised, for the marginalized and for all of her district,

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:40.000
but she's also been the voice that spoke in truth to power and she did that and she continues

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:41.000
to do that.

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:46.000
She plans on doing that and I want people of America to know that Georgia is on the front

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:47.000
lines.

00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:51.000
We're fighting for voting rights as we always have and I'm proud to represent Park Cannon.

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:56.000
She's proud to stand up for what's right in Georgia and it's unfortunate what happened

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:02.000
to her but she's going to stand resolute and make sure that we don't go one step further

00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:08.000
backwards, that we don't go to 1850 or not 1950 but we stand up and protect our voting

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:09.000
rights.

